how do u teach a year old dog new tricks see i have this year old dog she is a lil pain to teach things to her so what is a good trick to teach my dog to do any thing like for ex sit jump play come go home stuff like that bribery give lessons right before you feed her when she cooperates and does what you want feed her right after the lesson if she doesn't do what you want wait a couple of hours before you feed her if she is at all intelligent she will pick up the connection if she isn't well then she probably won't be learning any new tricks go home is probably the easiest one to start with have her on a leash with your friend holding the leash tell her go home then the friend takes her home on the leash and feeds her immediately when they arrive even if the friend has to drag her there the first time after that do the same thing and as long as the dog is cooperative which she should be remembering that last time you told her go home and she went she got fed set her up for success successful lessons should end with food and or petting what a good dog is the dog's favorite thing to hear from her master i don't know why but they like that much more than just good dog successful lessons should not always end in food start with food and praise and petting go to praise and petting then just praise a dog isn't quite as smart as a pig so you can get away with that best wishes Dog training Obedience training Shaggy dog story Lisa the Vegetarian Dog agility Aerial (dance move) The Amber Spyglass Kim Possible Humphrey Bogart Teacher's Pet (Disney) Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Paranoia Agent Spidey Super Stories Falconry Blonde on Blonde Kodocha Futurama (TV series - season 5) Characters of Naruto Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Ranma __ characters Kender Dean Koontz Back to the Future timeline The Inside Time Out of Mind Aladdin (1992 film) Kitesurfing The Fairly OddParents Pig Garfield Blood on the Tracks Friends Sinfest Se